Aminic Antioxidants

Antioxidants are vital components in the prevention of lubricant oxidative degradation due to exposure to oxygen, heat, light and metals during storage and service.












Products
 













Naugalube® 403

​Naugalube® 403 provides excellent oxidation stability in a wide range of petroleum products, and is especially effective as an antioxidant in fuels and with vegetable oil based lubricants.






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® 438L

​Naugalube® 438L is a nonylated diphenylamine for use as an antioxidant in mineral and synthetic base stocks that are typically employed in lubricant applications. Its liquid form allows for easy handling and blending. Naugalube 438L can easily be incorporated into engine oils, gear oils, hydraulic fluids, turbine oils, and greases. 






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® 640

​Naugalube® 640 is an octylated, butylated diphenylamine antioxidant for use in mineral and synthetic base stocks that are typically employed in lubricant applications. Its high nitrogen content and liquid form allows for incorporation into high performance passenger car and diesel engine oils, automatic transmission fluids, marine diesel oils, industrial oils and greases. 






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® 680

​Naugalube® 680is a low-volatility alkylated diphenylamine antioxidant which provides excellent oxidation stability to mineral oils and synthetic fluids. Its features include low volatility, clear reddish color, and a high nitrogen content. Naugalube 680 has shown applicability in passenger car engine oils, aviation turbine oils, and industrial oils.






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® 750

​Naugalube 750 is a mixed butyl, octyl diphenylamine antioxidant for use in lubricants formulated with mineral and synthetic base stocks.






Technical Data SheetNaugalube 750 Commercial






Naugalube® AMS

​Naugalube® AMS is a high molecular weight amine antioxidant which provides excellent oxidation stability to both mineral oils and synthetic fluids.  Naugalube AMS has show applicability in automatic transmission fluids, diesel engine oils and industrial oils. 






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® APAN

​Naugalube® APAN is a powerful, long lasting, low sludging antioxidant, which provides excellent stability in a wide range of petroleum products. It is especially cost effective antioxidant in service applications for turbine oils, compressor oils and hydraulic oils, where low color and longevity is desired. 






Technical Data Sheet






Naugalube® TMQ

​Naugalube® TMQ is an especially effective antioxidant in ester containing fluids and grease formulations. It can be easily incorporated into gear oils, turbine oils, hydraulic fluids compressor oils and greases. 






Technical Data Sheet






Naugard® PANA

​Naugard® PANA, phenyl-alpha-naphthylamine, is an excellent antioxidant for synthetic fluids and mineral oils. It is particularly useful in high temperature applications, such as aviation turbine engine oils, and in the formulation of high performance industrial oils and greases.






Technical Data Sheet









 
















































